Hey Flavio,

This looks interesting. Could open the door for parallel downloads and such.

I'm wondering if there's a slight mis-match with the referenced blueprint? 

 > In order to avoid polluting the API, this logic should be  
 > limited to the service->backend leg (as opposed to end-to-
 > end interaction from the client side).

That seems to mean something like this: https://review.openstack.org/#/c/48913/

where I think you're going for the more ambitious glance API change.
